-- Pannergy Rises to Four-Month High on 1 Billion-Forint Subsidy
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-09-24T15:28:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/pannergy-heads-for-four-month-high-on-1-billion-forint-subsidy.html
Pannergy (PANNERGY)  Nyrt., a Hungarian
renewable energy company, climbed to the highest in more than
four months after receiving a  subsidy  of 1 billion forint ($4.5
million) for a geothermal project.  The shares rose as much as 1.3 percent and traded 0.5
percent up at 621 forint by the close in Budapest, the highest
since May 7. The benchmark BUX stock index advanced 0.3 percent.  The subsidy Pannergy obtained is equivalent to 46 forint
per share, more than the eight forints the stock rose on Sept.
21, the day of the announcement, analysts at Erste Group Bank AG
in Budapest wrote in a research report today.  “We view the news as positive,” Peter Szentirmai, a
Budapest-based analyst at the broker unit of KBC Groep NV, wrote
in an e-mailed report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
